				\begin{document}$$\rm {\text{BaCe}}_{{{\text{0}}{\text{.90}}}} {\text{Yb}}_{{0.10}} {\text{O}}_{{3 - \delta }} $$\end{document} (BCYb10) thin films synthesized through a combined EDTA-citrate complexing method, underwent phase segregation in an asymmetric atmosphere and failed to maintain a perovskite structure at the surface [24].

This group includes the range of salts and acids pertaining to the heteroatom oxo-anions of sulphate, selenate, phosphate, arsenate, nitrate, etc. In the anhydrous state, these compounds are able to conduct protons due to self-dissociation and the hopping or jumping mechanism of protons among hetero-oxo ions (e.g., \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
